    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0157">
<l>melleḻuttu mikuvaḻi valippoṭu tōṉṟalum</l>
<l>valleḻuttu mikuvaḻi melippoṭu tōṉṟalu</l>
<l>miyaṟkai maruṅkiṉ mikaṟkai tōṉṟalu</l>
<l>muyirmika varuvaḻi uyirkeṭa varutaluñ</l>
<l>cāriyai yuḷvaḻic cāriyai keṭutaluñ</l>
<l>cāriyai yuḷvaḻit taṉṉurupu nilaiyalum</l>
<l>cāriyai yiyaṟkai yuṟaḻat tōṉṟalu</l>
<l>muyartiṇai maruṅki ṉoḻiyātu varutalu</l>
<l>maḵṟiṇai viravuppeyark kavviya ṉilaiyalu</l>
<l>meypiṟi tākiṭat tiyaṟkai yātalu</l>
<l>maṉṉa piṟavun taṉṉiyaṉ maruṅkiṉ</l>
<l>meypeṟak kiḷantu poruḷvarain ticaikku</l>
<l>maikāra vēṟṟumait tiripeṉa moḻipa</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>If a noun [with its third case-marker dropped]</l>
<l>ends in a vowel or a non-vocalised consonant,</l>
<l>and is followed by a verb which denotes its action</l>
<l>[and] which begins with a plosive that admits</l>
<l>its doubling, there exist two proper ways</l>
<l>[of sandhi] - no change, or the optional</l>
<l>appearance of consonants ; one should study it</l>
<l>carefully in the chapter on cases.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
